# Compliance Evidence Rules (NHS + HIPAA + ISO 27001 readiness)

## Required Evidence Artifacts
- Threat model and data flow diagrams must exist in docs/compliance/.
- Audit log policy and retention/deletion policy must exist.
- For each mapped control, provide:
  - implementation location (file paths)
  - how to generate evidence artifact (command/output)
  - operational procedure if applicable

## NHS Readiness
- Maintain DTAC mapping doc and keep it updated.
- Maintain DSPT readiness mapping.
- Maintain clinical risk management plan (developer-side).

## HIPAA Readiness
- Maintain HIPAA Security Rule mapping focusing on administrative, physical, technical safeguards.
- Maintain access controls, audit controls, integrity controls, transmission security evidence.

## ISO 27001 Readiness
- Maintain an ISMS evidence structure under docs/compliance/isms/
- Include risk register template, control mapping, incident response plan.

## Build-time Evidence Generation
- Evidence packs, audit exports, and access logs must be generatable by commands, not manual edits.
